CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Chain Restaurants – Sodium and Added Sugars Warning Icons
3 and Disclosure and Notice
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Department of Health to adopt certain
5 regulations relating to the sale of food items with a high added sugars content or
6 high sodium content by a chain restaurant by a certain date and to administer a
7 certain continuing education campaign within a certain time direct chain
8 restaurants to its website for a certain purpose; requiring certain chain restaurants
9 to display certain icons next to food items with a high added sugars content or high
10 sodium content and a certain disclosure and notice on each menu or menu board; and
11 generally relating to chain restaurants and high sodium and added sugars menu
12 icons menu items with high sodium and added sugars.
13 BY renumbering
14 Article – Health – General
15 Section 21–330.3 and 21–330.4
16 to be Section 21–330.4 and 21–330.5, respectively
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
20 Article – Education
21 Section 13–517(a)(1)
